section#portfolio.content-section(data-magellan-destination='portfolio', name='portfolio')
  .portfolio-container
    hgroup.section-header
      h2 Portfolio
      h3.subheader Investing all that I am into all that I do
    .portfolio-items
    
      .portfolio-item.odd
        .portfolio-screenshot
          a(href="http://blog.prosper.community/our-journey-to-build-refugee-projects-com/")
            img(src="images/refugee-projects.jpg", alt="refugee projects portfolio image" data-interchange='[images/refugee-projects.jpg, (default)], [images/refugee-projects@2x.jpg, (retina)]')
        .portfolio-excerpt
          hgroup.portfolio-heading
            h3 RefugeeProjects.com
            h5.subheader Digital Humanitarian Work: Product Owner
          p I led a distributed team of over 90 digital workers to research, design and develop a central database of over 1,500 refugee crisis initiatives. In just a few months we launched a working MVP that has been used by a wide range of actors across the crisis, including refugees, volunteers, 
            a(href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/mediaaction") BBC Media Action
            |  and 
            a(href="http://techfugees.com/" ) Techfugees
            | .
          a.cta(href="http://blog.prosper.community/our-journey-to-build-refugee-projects-com/") Read Retrospective
      
      .portfolio-item
        .portfolio-screenshot
          a(href="http://prosper.community")
            img(src="images/prosper.jpg", alt="prosper portfolio image" data-interchange='[images/prosper.jpg, (default)], [images/prosper@2x.jpg, (retina)]')
        .portfolio-excerpt
          hgroup.portfolio-heading
            h3 Prosper
            h5.subheader Digital Humanitarian Work: Founder
          p As a response to the crisis in Europe, I founded a community of digital workers around the belief that 
            em "When refugees prosper, we all prosper"
            | . In four months the team grew from one person to ninety, and we successfuly launched an open source platform to help refugees, volunteers and donors find projects that meet their needs: 
            a(href="http://refugeeprojects.com") RefugeeProjects.com
          a.cta(href="/prosper.html") View The Case Study
        
      .portfolio-item.odd
        .portfolio-screenshot
          a(href="https://90days.john-ellison.com")
            img(src="images/clearleft-training-project.jpg", alt="working with the team at Clearleft on a three-month workplacement" data-interchange='[images/clearleft-training-project.jpg, (default)], [images/clearleft-training-project@2x.jpg, (retina)]').radius
        .portfolio-excerpt
          hgroup.portfolio-heading
            h3 Clearleft
            h5.subheader UX Research, Strategy &amp; Design
          p I worked with a team of user experience designers at 
            a(href="http://clearleft.com/") Clearleft
            |  to research and define new business concepts within the landscape of design training. I designed and facilitated story-driven workshops to shape the narrative of our design process. I helped pitch the new business opportunities to Clearleft executives and celebreated as several of the concepts were taken on by the organization.
          a.cta(href="https://90days.john-ellison.com") Read The Blog

      .portfolio-item
        .portfolio-screenshot
          a(href="/thengine.html")
            img(src="images/thengine-galaxy-grey-bg.jpg", alt="screenshot of thengine's homepage on samsung galaxy")
        .portfolio-excerpt
          hgroup.portfolio-heading
            h3 Thengine
            h5.subheader UX Research &amp; Design
          p I led research and design for a startup out of the Founders Institute based in Denver, Colorado. From user interviews to prototyping and usability testing, I helped shape the vision and execution of a seed-funded startup that created tools for local musicians and their fans.
          a.cta(href="/thengine.html") View Case Study

      .portfolio-item.odd
        .portfolio-screenshot
          a(href="/sprky-chess.html")
            img(src="images/sprky-imac.jpg", alt="screenshot of sprky chess app on an imac" data-interchange='[images/sprky-imac.jpg, (default)], [images/sprky-imac@2x.jpg, (retina)]')
        .portfolio-excerpt
          hgroup.portfolio-heading
            h3 SPRKY Chess
            h5.subheader Full-Stack, Ruby on Rails
          p For the capstone of The Firehose Project, we crafted an open source chess app using Ruby on Rails. With Test-Driven Development (TDD) as our guide, we built every element of the application&mdash;from the back-end Ruby to the front-end Javascript. The project was featured in 
            a(href="http://www.huffingtonpost.com/ken-mazaika/when-the-heck-did-learning-to-code-become-cool_b_7471938.html") an article on the Huffington Post.
          a.cta(href="/sprky-chess.html") View Case Study
          
